edu.ucsc.cross.hse.core.variable

Interface Variable<X>

  • Type Parameters:
    X - the stored variable of type X
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DependentVariable, DynamicVariable, RandomVariable

    public interface Variable<X>
    An interface that is used to implement structures that are capable of doing different things using pointer protection. This can provide access to the current version dynamically data set or element within a data set, allowing system outputs to be configured outside the system itself. The implementations in this package demonstrate some features. Intended Operator: User
